         heh it's people trying to get xp at raids that cause undue deaths and your usual stupidity (overnuking by casters, poor/no aggro control by melee, etc) that can wipe the raid out in multi-mob encounters.</P><P>Impressive changes, tho.  Really excited to see them go in.</P><P>This isn't a gripe in any way or sorts, but perhaps a time-saving suggestion while the pet coding is being mauled: Not too long ago pets were made to poof after its owner was FD for more than two minutes.  Now that pets won't aggro, I wonder if it'd be possible to lift that part of the code out.  But it's really a minor detail that's not necessary with changes of this scope; it'd only save a bone chip and a few seconds worth of med time.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
